\v 40 and one kid of the goats for a sin offering. 
\v 41 And for a sacrifice of peace offering, two heifers, five rams, five he-goats, five ewe lambs of a year old: this \add was\add* the gift of Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai. 
\p
\v 42 On the sixth day the prince of the sons of Gad, Eliasaph the son of Reuel. 
\v 43  \add He brought\add* his gift, one silver charger, its weight a hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels according to the holy shekel; both full of fine flour kneaded with oil for a meat offering. 
\v 44 One golden censer of ten shekels, full of incense. 
\v 45 One calf of the herd, one ram, one he-lamb of a year old for a whole burnt offering, 
\v 46 and one kid of the goats for a sin offering. 
\v 47 And for a sacrifice of peace offering, two heifers, five rams, five he-goats, five ewe lambs of a year old: this \add was\add* the gift of Eliasaph the son of Reuel. 
\p
\v 48 On the seventh day the prince of the sons of Ephraim, Elishama the son of Ammihud. 
\v 49  \add He brought\add* his gift, one silver charger, its weight was a hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels according to the holy shekel; both full of fine flour kneaded with oil for a meat offering. 
\v 50 One golden censer of ten shekels, full of incense. 
\v 51 One calf of the herd, one ram, one he-lamb of a year old for a whole burnt offering, 
\v 52 and one kid of the goats for a sin offering. 
\v 53 And for a sacrifice of peace offering, two heifers, five rams, five he-goats, five ewe lambs of a year old: this \add was\add* the gift of Elishama the son of Ammihud. 
\p
\v 54 On the eighth day the prince of the sons of Manasseh, Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur. 
\v 55  \add He brought\add* his gift, one silver charger, its weight one hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels according to the holy shekel; both full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering. 
\v 56 One golden censer of ten shekels, full of incense. 
\v 57 One calf of the herd, one ram, one he-lamb of a year old for a whole burnt offering, 
\v 58 and one kid of the goats for a sin offering. 
\v 59 And for a sacrifice of peace offering two heifers, five rams, five he-goats, five ewe lambs of a year old: this \add was\add* the gift of Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur. 
\p
\v 60 On the ninth day the prince of the sons of Benjamin, Abidan the son of Gideoni. 
